Sentencas: Anode-supported cone-shaped tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are successfully fabricated by a single-step cosintering process.
Titulo: Fabrication and Electrochemical Performance of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by a Single-Step Cosintering Process

Sentencas: The cone-shaped tubular single cell, NiO+YSZ/YSZ/LSM+YSZ/LSM, is comprised of a Ni+yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode, YSZ electrolyte, a La0.7Sr0.3MnO3 (LSM)+YSZ cathode layer, and an LSM cathode current collector layer.
Titulo: Fabrication and Electrochemical Performance of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by a Single-Step Cosintering Process

Sentencas: The fabrication process involves slip casting of the anode, colloidal spray coating of the electrolyte, slurry coating of the cathode, and single-step cosintering of the cone-shaped tubular cells in the temperature range of 1200 degrees-1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and Electrochemical Performance of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by a Single-Step Cosintering Process

Sentencas: The cells are tested with humidified hydrogen (75 mL/min) as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Fabrication and Electrochemical Performance of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by a Single-Step Cosintering Process

Sentencas: Cell electrochemical test results and scanning electron microscope graphs show that the optimal temperature of the single-step cosintering process is 1300 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and Electrochemical Performance of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by a Single-Step Cosintering Process
